Name: Domestic Ruffler Foot
Short description: Ruffler foot is sewing tools used for sewing small pleats on fabrics to form ruffles. It's usually used on domestic, manual blackhead tabletop and zig zag sewing machines.
Description:
The Ruffler Foot is one of the most time saving attachments you can add to your sewing machine. This accessory is used to create perfectly spaced pleats and gathers.

Simply turn the adjustment on the foot to change the depth of the pleats. Change the setting to adjust the number of stitches between the pleats. Meaning, the foot will do all the work for you – a true time-saver.

You can easily add a frill onto aprons, curtains, bedding or a range of projects and save a heap of time. Add a touch of class with ease by simply adding this foot to your collection and create perfectly even ruffles.

With the Ruffler Foot, there’s no need to pin the gathers or use elastic to create fabulous-looking ruffles.

This particular foot showcased here works for domestic manual blackhead sewing machines and  tabletop zig zag sewing machines.

Fits most low shank machines.

https://youtube.com/shorts/pG_e7fx-0Ww?feature=share
Categories: Sewing Machine Foot > Manual Blackhead Foots, Sewing Machine Foot, Sewing Machine Foot > Tabletop Foots & Attachments
Refined Description:
The Ruffler Foot is a time-saving attachment for your sewing machine, perfect for creating evenly spaced pleats and gathers. Adjust the foot to change the depth of the pleats and the number of stitches between them. Let the foot do the work for you, saving you time and effort. 

Easily add frills to aprons, curtains, bedding, and more with this accessory. Enhance your projects with perfectly even ruffles by simply adding this foot to your collection. No need to pin gathers or use elastic with the Ruffler Foot.

This foot is compatible with domestic manual blackhead sewing machines and tabletop zig zag sewing machines, fitting most low shank machines. Check out this video to see it in action: https://youtube.com/shorts/pG_e7fx-0Ww?feature=share.

Name: Tabletop 7Pieces Hemming Foot Set
Description:
Hemming feet are used to create neat, professional hems on fabric. 
Wide hem feet
Can create double-folded hems without the need for pinning, pressing, or marking. The foot has a guide with a brick folder that pre-folds the fabric before it reaches the presser foot. 
Hemmer feet
Can be used to create hems on light to medium weight fabrics, such as scarves, light skirts, or dresses. 
Here are some tips for using a hemming foot:
  • Adjust the needle position to the left and elongate the stitch length. 
  • Iron medium weight fabrics before feeding them through the presser foot. 
  • Use your fingers to gently guide the fabric through the presser foot. 
Seven sizes of hemming attachments for domestic tabletop sewing machines : 2/8, 3/8, 4/8, 5/8, 6/8, 7/8 and 8/8 of an inch respectively.

Name: Blackhead Manual Machine Teflon Foot
Short description: Used to sew leather, delicate fabrics, slippery fabrics, thick fabrics and more.
Description:
A Teflon foot, also known as a non-stick foot, is used for sewing fabrics that tend to stick to a regular presser foot, such as vinyl, leather, suede, and plastic. The Teflon coating on the bottom of the foot allows the fabric to glide smoothly, preventing it from tugging against the foot. 
Here are some uses for a Teflon foot:
  • Home decor projects: When making home decor projects that use upholstery fabrics with backings 
  • Clear windows: When sewing vinyl for a clear window, a standard foot can drag and make it difficult to get good stitching 
  • Slippery fabrics: When sewing slippery fabrics, a Teflon foot makes it easy

Name: Blackhead Manual Machine Compensating Foot
Short description: Compensating presser foot is used for creating an even stitch along the edge of the material
Description:
A compensating presser foot is used for sewing even stitches along the edge of fabric, top stitching, and more: 
  • Sewing even stitches
    A compensating foot can create even stitches 1/16 in from the edge of the fabric. 
  • Top stitching
    A compensating foot is useful for top stitching close to the edge of a zipper or bag. 
  • Sewing through different thicknesses
    A compensating foot can go over different thicknesses of fabric. The larger toe of the foot sits against the feed dogs while the fabric sits under the foot. 
  • Stabilizing stitching
    A compensating foot can stabilize stitching 1.5 mm to the right or left of a thick seam. 
  • Using as a seam guide
    A compensating foot can be used with a gauge to get an accurate seam allowance.
Categories: Sewing Machine Foot > Manual Blackhead Foots, Sewing Machine Foot
Refined Description: A compensating presser foot is utilized for sewing even stitches along the fabric's edge, top stitching, and more. It can create even stitches 1/16 inch from the edge of the fabric and is useful for top stitching near zippers or bags. This foot can also sew through different fabric thicknesses, with the larger toe against the feed dogs and the fabric underneath. Additionally, it can stabilize stitching 1.5 mm to the right or left of a thick seam and be used with a gauge for precise seam allowances.

Name: Singer 14HD854 Heavy Duty Serger
Description:
Heavy duty metal frame and larger cutting knife provides extra durability and cuts through thicker fabrics with ease. For your convenience, your machine will arrive pre-threaded. Accessories included are located in the storage area at the front of your machine.  
Built-In Stitches (8)
Choose from a variety of stitches for basic sewing, decorative sewing, and more
Adjustable Stitch Length (+)
Customize the appearance of a stitch by increasing or decreasing the distance between stitches. Use this function for various stitch techniques like applique, basting and more.
Adjustable Stitch Width ()
The size of the stitch from left to right is adjustable, to make the stitch sew narrower or wider as desired.
Thread Capability (2-3-4)
Choose from seams finishes, hem finishes and decorative edges thanks to a variety of stitch combinations available.
Color Coded Threading System (+)
Threading path for each thread is indicated with a specific color to simplify the threading process. Handy reference diagrams are also included right on the machine.
Differential Feed (+)
Controls the ratio of movement between the front and back sections of the feed teeth. Use this to help remove distortion from seams in stretchy fabrics or puckers from seams in lightweight or silky fabrics.
Built-In Rolled Hem (4)
Just slide a lever to easily convert the machine for rolled hem sewing - no need to change stitch plate
Movable Upper Knife (+)
Upper knife can be engaged to trim excess seam allowance as you sew, or it can be rolled out of the way for special techniques like flatlocking or anytime when you don't want the machine to trim
Heavy Duty Metal Frame (+)
The machine's interior frame is metal, providing long lasting durability
High Speed Stitching (1300/min)
Professional speed for faster results.
Speed Control (Digital)
Set the maximum sewing speed of the machine
LED Lighting (+)
Long lasting LED lighting provides bright illumination and stays cool to the touch
Free Arm (+)
Slide off the Removable Storage Compartment for access to the free arm, making it easy to sew trouser hems, sleeve cuffs and other smaller or tubular projects
Extra High Presser Foot Lifter (+)
Presser foot has an extra high position available to accommodate thick fabrics.
Amps (1)
Watts (120)
Volts (220)
Hz (60)

Name: Singer Promise 1409 Tabletop Sewing Machine
Description:
Sew with ease for almost any project with the Singer Promise 1409 Sewing Machine! With basic, decorative and buttonhole stitching included, this machine offers all the essential features you'll need and is perfect for sewing beginners. The Singer Promise 1408 can sew many layers of fabric and take on even heavy fabrics, making it ideal for a wide range of sewing patterns and projects. There are eight built-in stitches available, so whether your purpose is fashion design, garment repairs, home décor or quilting, this machine has you covered! The stitches include buttonhole, straight, zigzag, blind hems, rick rack, scallop and rampart. Set-up is easier than ever with this machine, as you have an automatic bobbin winder and simple machine threading. There is a reverse lever to allow for automatic stitch locking. In the accessory storage drawer, you will find four presser feet: general, buttonhole, button sewing and zipper. These are easily removable, making it effortless to switch them over or to create a free arm for stitching in hard-to-reach areas. Machine features:

  • 63 stitch applications
  • Easy stitch selection dial

  • Maximum stitch length: 4.2mm
  • Maximum stitch width: 4mm
  • Front loading bobbin

  • Built-in storage
  • Quick and easy threading
  • Accessory storage drawer
  • Automatic bobbin winding
  • Darning plate
  • Free arm
  • Heavy duty metal frame
  • Reverse operation
  • Two-year manufacturer's guarantee
  • Mains powered by a UK plug

Name: Wooden Bead Spinner
Description:
It is basically a bowl on a spindle. The spindle allows the bowl to spin. So, when you fill it with seed beads, you can spin it around.

Centrifugal force pushes the beads into a stream at the edges of the bowl. So, if you stick a piece of wire, or a long needle into these beads, then a steady stream of beads will flow up your wire/needle and thread.

You can use a bead spinner any time you want to thread a large quantity of seed beads.

https://youtube.com/shorts/dmINt65Yhjk?feature=share
Refined Description: A bead spinner is a tool consisting of a bowl attached to a spindle, allowing the bowl to spin when filled with seed beads. Centrifugal force causes the beads to flow towards the edges of the bowl, creating a steady stream when a wire or needle is inserted. This makes threading a large quantity of seed beads quick and easy. Watch how it works here: https://youtube.com/shorts/dmINt65Yhjk?feature=share.

Name: 6in1 Stitch & Stick Guide
Description: The 6-in-1 Stick ‘n Stitch Guide is a truly multi-function tool that will make sewing even the most difficult and demanding applications of thread to fabric a breeze. The stitch guide itself is a two-piece interlocking plastic foot. They can be used together or separately depending on your stitching application. Connection with your sewing machine is accomplished by a renewable adhesive attached permanently to the bottom of each foot. Just remove the seam guide feet from your machine when you’re done. They leave no adhesive residue. Washing the adhesive surface on the guide foot with dish soap renews the surface and its adhesive properties. The shapes and edges of each guide foot makes it perfect for a multitude of sewing applications. The included grid template measures placement from the needle position and ensures that the stitch guide is always just where we want it. So, how’s it used? Unlike other seam guides, the Stick ‘n Stitch Guide does way more than provide a single seam allowance. In fact its innovative design provides us with six different primary applications. 1. The two sections can be used either singly or together for straight stitching 2. We can place one foot on either side of the needle for fast, error free quilt strips or precision placement top stitches. 3. Place the curve side up in a position in front of the presser foot for outer curves. 4. Place the curve side down in a position in front of the presser foot for inner curves 5. Straight stitch on the right side. 6. Straight stitch on the left side.
Categories: Sewing Machine Foot > Industrial Foots & Attachments, Sewing Machine Foot > Manual Blackhead Foots, Sewing Machine Foot, Sewing Machine Foot > Tabletop Foots & Attachments
Refined Description:
The 6-in-1 Stick ‘n Stitch Guide is a versatile tool that simplifies even the most challenging sewing tasks. This stitch guide consists of two interlocking plastic feet that can be used together or separately depending on your stitching needs. The feet connect to your sewing machine using a reusable adhesive that leaves no residue when removed. Simply wash the adhesive surface with dish soap to renew its stickiness.

The unique shapes and edges of each guide foot make them perfect for a variety of sewing applications. The included grid template helps you measure placement from the needle position, ensuring precise stitching every time. Unlike other seam guides, the Stick ‘n Stitch Guide offers six primary applications:

1. Use the two sections together or separately for straight stitching.
2. Place one foot on each side of the needle for quick, accurate quilt strips or precise top stitches.
3. Position the curve side up for outer curves.
4. Position the curve side down for inner curves.
5. Stitch straight on the right side.
6. Stitch straight on the left side.

This innovative tool is a must-have for any sewing enthusiast looking to achieve professional results with ease.

Name: Tailor’s Clapper
Description: A tailor's clapper is a flat block of hardwood, often rounded on the ends with routed grooves along the sides for finger holds. It works by absorbing the steam applied to a seam, and locking in the heat. As you press down on the seam with the clapper, the pressure sets the seam flat as the fabric cools. So, if you like to have flat seams when you sew (I know I do) then this humble tool can help you! They are made from hardwood, as they need to be close grained to work their magic. https://youtube.com/shorts/iSjmNN_Tat8?feature=share

Name: Antique Bead Spinner
Description:
Ideal for string seed beads, liquid silver beads, or other small beads with speed and ease.

An excellent time saver bead stringing tool -- much faster than stringing small beads by hand. Picks the beads up quickly and you can finish projects faster!

Fill the bowl about half-full of beads, and then spin. insert a curved big eye beading needle into the spinning beads and watch them jump onto the needle.

The beads nest all on their own - when ample beads are on the needle, then move them to the connected stringing material and dip the needle back into the spinning beads to load on another few-inch.

Made of beech, resin, and stainless steel materials of excellent quality, with smooth and delicate texture, excellent feeling, rust-proof and durable.

Refined Description:
This bead stringing tool is perfect for stringing seed beads, liquid silver beads, or other small beads quickly and easily. It is a great time-saving tool, much faster than stringing beads by hand. The tool picks up beads quickly, allowing you to finish projects faster.

To use, fill the bowl about half-full with beads, then spin the bowl. Insert a curved big eye beading needle into the spinning beads and watch as they jump onto the needle. The beads will naturally nest on the needle. Once you have enough beads on the needle, move them onto your stringing material. Dip the needle back into the spinning beads to load on another few inches.

This tool is made of high-quality beech, resin, and stainless steel materials, giving it a smooth and delicate texture. It provides an excellent feeling, is rust-proof, and durable.

Name: Rectangle Rhinestone Flipper
Description:
With just a shake, flat back stones will turn right side up, quickly and easily!

The textured surface design of the tray uses friction to flip your stones just like magic!

They'll turn flat side down ready to be put into place, saving you time and aggravation.

The Magical Tray is designed for use with your favorite flat back stones up to size ss12.

1. Place stones in tray. A small number of stones works best.

2. Shake gently in a circular motion until the stones begin to turn over.

If static prevents small beads from moving smoothly, nudge them closer to the center of the tray and try again.

When you learn to shake the tray correctly most stones will quickly turn over, however, even after shaking properly some beads could remain upside-down.

Intended for use with flat back rhinestones ss12 and smaller.

https://youtube.com/shorts/TIuR29SFYds?feature=share
Refined Description:
Easily turn flat back stones right side up with just a shake using the Magical Tray! Its textured surface design creates friction to magically flip stones for quick placement. Designed for up to size ss12 stones, this tray saves time and frustration.

To use:
1. Place stones in tray, preferably a small number at a time.
2. Gently shake in a circular motion until stones flip over. If static causes issues, adjust stones and try again.

While most stones will flip over with correct shaking, some may require extra nudging. Ideal for flat back rhinestones ss12 and smaller. Watch the magic in action: https://youtube.com/shorts/TIuR29SFYds?feature=share

Name: Big Wooden Bead Spinner
Description:
It is basically a bowl on a spindle. The spindle allows the bowl to spin. So, when you fill it with seed beads, you can spin it around.

Centrifugal force pushes the beads into a stream at the edges of the bowl. So, if you stick a piece of wire, or a long needle into these beads, then a steady stream of beads will flow up your wire/needle and thread.

You can use a bead spinner any time you want to thread a large quantity of seed beads.
Refined Description: The bead spinner is a bowl on a spindle that allows for easy spinning. Simply fill the bowl with seed beads and spin it to utilize centrifugal force, which pushes the beads to the edges. Insert a piece of wire or long needle into the beads to create a steady stream for threading. Perfect for threading large quantities of seed beads quickly and effortlessly.

Name: Semi Automatic Eyelet Machine
Description: [embed]https://youtu.be/VbLtq2NLrpc[/embed] This semi-automatic eyelet machine takes all of the hard work out of setting eyelets/grommets, Compatible with 8mm, self-punching eyelets (available separately). Simply pour the eyelets into the hopper and they will automatically feed down the channel. When you pull down on the lever, the die ‘picks up’ an eyelet before fixing to the fabric. This semi-automatic eyelet machine simplifies the process of setting eyelets/grommets and is compatible with 8mm self-punching eyelets (sold separately). With one action, the machine can punch a hole and attach 6mm eyelets to your fabric, setting up to 1800 eyelets per hour with minimal effort.

The machine features a hopper that can hold up to 500 eyelets at once, a deep throat depth of 165mm, and a durable powder-coated iron construction. It eliminates the need to manually set a grommet on a die before each use - simply pour the eyelets into the hopper for automatic feeding.

Easy to use with an extra-long handle and soft-touch grip, this machine is set on rollers for effortless movement along your project. Perfect for corsets, DIY projects, leathercraft, handbags, clothing, scrapbooking, documents, and more, it is suitable for both home and professional use.

Name: Gravity Steam Iron Thermostat Set
Description:
The main function of thermostat in an electric iron is to make sure that the iron doesn’t get too hot if it is left unattended to for a period of time. When electric current is passed through a coil in an electric iron, the coil becomes very hot. Through conduction the heat is transferred to the flat base plate of the electric iron which is used to iron our clothes . However, the heating element continues to get hotter so far there is continuous drawing of electricity from the power supply. This result into a lot of energy wastage, cloths ruin and in the worst scenario, cause nasty accident. At this point, thermostat comes in because it is important that the iron doesn’t heat up to temperature that is hazardous.
  • Precise Temperature Control: The Thermostat is specially designed , providing precise temperature control for your ironing needs.
  • Optimal Ironing Results: Achieve perfect results with the ability to set and maintain the ideal temperature, ensuring smooth and wrinkle-free ironing on various fabrics.
  • Easy Installation: Simple to install, the thermostat allows you to upgrade your iron quickly, so you can get back to tackling your ironing tasks efficiently.
Refined Description:
The thermostat in an electric iron functions to prevent overheating when the iron is left unattended. When electric current passes through a coil, it heats up and transfers heat to the iron's base plate for ironing clothes. However, continuous electricity consumption causes the heating element to keep getting hotter, leading to energy wastage, damaged clothes, and potential accidents. The thermostat is crucial in ensuring the iron does not reach hazardous temperatures. 

- Precise Temperature Control: The thermostat offers accurate temperature control for optimal ironing results.
- Optimal Ironing Results: Set and maintain the ideal temperature for smooth and wrinkle-free ironing on different fabrics.
- Easy Installation: Quickly upgrade your iron with the easy-to-install thermostat for efficient ironing tasks.

Name: Magnetic Sewing Machine Laser Positioning Light
Description:
A magnetic sewing machine laser positioning light can be used for a variety of sewing and crafting projects, including:
  • Creating straight lines
    A laser line can be used to sew straight lines, such as for half-square triangles (HSTs) or stitch-and-flip corners. 
  • Centering designs
    A laser can help center designs for embroidery, quilting, or other projects. 
  • Finding starting points
    A laser can help you find your exact starting point for a project. 
  • Marking points
    A laser can be used to mark a point on your fabric where you want your needle to go. 
This magnetic sewing machine laser positioning lights have the following features:
  • Magnetic base
    A magnetic base allows you to attach the light to any metal surface on your sewing machine or cutting machine.
  • Adjustability
    Lights are 360-degree adjustable so you can position them exactly where you need them.
  • Collimated beam
    A collimated beam helps focus the light, reducing eye strain and improving visibility.
This light has a cross beam.
Refined Description:
A magnetic sewing machine laser positioning light can enhance various sewing and crafting projects by:
- Creating straight lines for precise stitching like half-square triangles (HSTs) and stitch-and-flip corners.
- Centering designs accurately for embroidery, quilting, and other projects.
- Finding exact starting points for your projects.
- Marking points on fabric to guide your needle placement.

Key features of this magnetic sewing machine laser positioning light include:
- Magnetic base for easy attachment to any metal surface on your sewing or cutting machine.
- 360-degree adjustability for precise positioning.
- Collimated beam for focused light, reducing eye strain and improving visibility.

Additionally, this light features a cross beam for added functionality.

Name: Industrial Special Cording Rolling Foot
Description:
An Industrial Special Cording Rolling Foot, also known as a cording foot or piping foot, is used to sew cording, piping, or zippers neatly and smoothly, especially on industrial sewing machines, and it is designed to prevent fabric slippage and feed difficult materials. 
  • Roller: The foot features a roller (or rollers) that helps to feed the fabric smoothly and prevent slippage, especially when sewing over seams or uneven surfaces. 
  • Versatility: Some models can be used as zipper feet, cording feet, or even standard presser feet. 
  • Smooth Sewing: The roller design ensures a smooth and even feed, leading to professional-looking results. 
  • Fabric Handling: It's ideal for working with difficult fabrics that can be prone to puckering or slipping. 
  • Precise Seam Placement: The foot helps to achieve precise seam placement, especially when sewing close to piping.
Categories: Sewing Machine Foot > Industrial Foots & Attachments, Sewing Machine Foot
Refined Description: The Industrial Special Cording Rolling Foot, also known as a cording foot or piping foot, is essential for neatly sewing cording, piping, or zippers on industrial sewing machines. It is designed to prevent fabric slippage and handle difficult materials, ensuring smooth and professional results. The foot features rollers that aid in feeding fabric smoothly over seams and uneven surfaces. Some models offer versatility as zipper feet, cording feet, or standard presser feet. This design ensures precise seam placement, especially when sewing near piping, and is ideal for working with fabrics prone to puckering or slipping.

Name: Industrial Adjustable Roller Unilateral Invisible Zipper Foot
Description:
An industrial roller unilateral invisible zipper foot is used for sewing invisible zippers on garments, allowing for a professional, seamless finish by guiding the zipper teeth and ensuring the needle stitches close to them.  This specialized presser foot is designed to sew invisible zippers, which are coil zippers where the elements are hidden behind the tape, making the zipper virtually invisible when closed. 
  • Benefits:
    • Precision: The foot allows for accurate stitching close to the zipper teeth, resulting in a neat and professional finish. 
    • Seamless Zipper: The foot helps create a seamless appearance, as the zipper is hidden and the seam is barely visible. 
    • Versatility: It's suitable for various garments like pants, dresses, skirts, blouses, and trousers, as well as home furnishings like pillowcases and cushions. 
  • How to use:
    • Attach the foot to your sewing machine, ensuring it is positioned correctly relative to the zipper teeth. 
    • Set your needle position to the middle to avoid striking the foot. 
    • Sew along the zipper, keeping the needle as close to the zipper teeth as possible. 
  • Other uses:
    While primarily designed for invisible zippers, a zipper foot can also be used for sewing piping or cording, and attaching other elements where sewing close to a raised edge is necessary.
Categories: Sewing Machine Foot > Industrial Foots & Attachments, Sewing Machine Foot
Refined Description:
An industrial roller unilateral invisible zipper foot is utilized for sewing invisible zippers on garments, ensuring a professional, seamless finish by guiding the zipper teeth and stitching close to them. This specialized presser foot is specifically designed for sewing invisible zippers, where the elements are concealed behind the tape, creating a virtually invisible closure. 

Benefits:
- Precision: The foot enables accurate stitching near the zipper teeth for a neat and professional outcome.
- Seamless Zipper: It helps achieve a seamless appearance by hiding the zipper and making the seam barely visible.
- Versatility: Suitable for various garments such as pants, dresses, skirts, blouses, trousers, as well as home furnishings like pillowcases and cushions.

How to use:
- Attach the foot to your sewing machine, ensuring correct positioning relative to the zipper teeth.
- Set the needle position to the middle to avoid hitting the foot.
- Sew along the zipper, keeping the needle as close to the zipper teeth as possible.

Other uses:
Although primarily designed for invisible zippers, a zipper foot can also be utilized for sewing piping, cording, and attaching other elements where sewing close to a raised edge is required.

Name: Industrial Sewing machine Wide Bias Attachment (Waist Band Folder)
Description:
An industrial sewing machine wide bias attachment, also known as a bias binder, is used to automatically fold and attach bias tape to fabric edges, creating a professional, finished look for hems, necklines, and other edges. 
  • Function:
    The attachment folds the bias tape around the fabric edge, and guides it into the stitching area, ensuring a clean and consistent finish. 
  • Benefits:
    • Speed and Efficiency: Automates the process of attaching bias tape, saving time and effort compared to manual methods. 
    • Precision: Creates uniform, professional-looking finishes. 
    • Versatility: Suitable for various projects, including clothing, quilting, and home décor. 
      How to Use:
      1. Prepare the Bias Tape: Cut the bias tape to the desired length. 
      2. Attach the Bias Binder: Install the bias binder foot on your industrial sewing machine. 
      3. Feed the Bias Tape: Feed the bias tape through the channels of the binder foot. 
      4. Sew: Stitch along the edge of the fabric, with the bias tape folded and guided by the binder foot. 
  • This bias attachment will give you an output of 1 inch tape suitable for cuffs and waist bands.
Refined Description:
The industrial sewing machine wide bias attachment, also known as a bias binder, automates the process of folding and attaching bias tape to fabric edges, creating a professional finish for hems, necklines, and other edges.

Name: Industrial Open Toe Free Motion Embroidery Quilting Presser Foot
Description: The Open Toe Free Motion Spring Foot gives clear visibility when doing free motion quilting or embroidery. Because of the open front, you can easily do stippling or follow a design in the fabric. The spring action keeps the fabric from lifting with the needle as the stitch is being formed which helps eliminate thread breakage with specialty or heavier threads. Be sure to use the appropriate needle for the thread you are using. The presser foot helps easily move up and down with the needle, especially play well on thick materials, liked hollow cotton, silk and so on. This spring-loaded foot helps avoid skipped stitches as the needle moves up and down with the foot. Fits for most industrial  straight stich sewing machine.
